ARGUMENT.

Nymph, sole lady without a peer‚ froin Kings descended, thou shinest by thine own light more than through thy noble race. Compared with thee one may deem that Darne Eloquence is mute, that Juno laclrs dignity, Venus grows dun, Minerva is rustic. Through thee the House of Keith enjoys an heir, who outshines all of his own age, and, though yet a youth, equals his great fore· fathers. 'Tis not lilre the Phrygian shepherd's gift the gift I offer, though thyself alone excel without a contest the Goddesses three. Receive the sacred songs with which the Holy Trinity, whose sacred flaine glows in thy breast, inspired of old the shepherds of Solyma. Receive what therein is ours, thou patroness of the poetic quire, to whom Helicon’s own streame are tributary. My Muse, poor erewhile and ragged and ready to expire, will get dignity and light and life from thee.
